                        My  yoga journey started with a great curiosity in Brighton in 2001. After many years of experience in being a regular and intensive yoga student, I received my first teacher training certificate from Mey Elbi in 2010, and then in 2011 I had the privilege of being Dona Farhi’s student in New Zealand.
                    </p>
                    <p style="margin-bottom:5px;">
                        I feel blessed with the trainings I received from very valuable teachers in the fields of yoga therapy, transformational breathing, mindfulness, meditation spiritualism, quantum healing, and Sufism.
                    </p>
                    <p style="margin-bottom:5px;">
                        In the last couple of years, I focused on private lessons rather than group lessons. The reason I prefer one to one sessions is to determine my yoga session according to the needs of my student. I like to offer my student not only yoga asanas but also other holistic methods. Receiving the results of this approach in a short time makes me even more passionate about what I do. That's why I don't just offer yoga in my classes. There are also deep breathing exercises and mindfulness protocols.
